CHIKUNGUNYA (50): INDONESIA: (CENTRAL JAVA)
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: Tue 9 Dec 2008
Source: Kompas.com [in Indonesian, machine trans., edited]
<http://www.kompas.com/read/xml/2008/12/09/14340620/boyolali.klb.chikungunya>


Due to the increasing number of areas having epidemics, in Boyolali
district, Central Java, an emergency has been declared due to a chikungunya
[virus] outbreak. This situation is believed to have occurred because of
the seasonal transition period has lasted an extremely long time, so that
the development of viral vectors that transmit this disease [virus] is favored.

During November [2008], 4 foci were discovered with the number of
chikungunya [virus infections] reaching 172 people and threatening the
other 1872 residents. Meanwhile, during 2008, 456 residents were recorded
to have had chikungunya virus infections. The usual seasonal transition
period is January until March, while the current transition period started
the month of September [2008].

"In no cases have the victims died because the disease does generally not
endanger lives. However, the economic impact is more striking than the
symptoms of dengue fever as chikungunya's effects remain afterward, with
pain in the joints and muscles that can last up to months, or even longer,"
said the head of field and disease prevention and environmental health, in
the District Health Office, Boyolali.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The chikungunya virus outbreak continues in Central Java in 2008.

An interactive map of Indonesia showing the location of Java can be
