******
[2]
Date: Fri 5 Dec 2008
Source: Kompas.com [in Indonesian, machine trans., edited]
<http://www.kompas.com/read/xml/2008/12/05/17292910/klb.chikungunya.di.purworejo>


The chikungunya outbreak spread in Pangenrejo Village, Kecamatan Purworejo,
Purworejo regency. Between 3 Nov 2008 and this Friday [5 Dec 2008], the
sufferers continued to spring up until the [case] data collected reached 47
people. Of this number, 12 people were still ill and 35 other people are
currently gradually recovering.

The head of the Field and Disease Prevention of the Office of Environmental
Health Sanitation of Purworejo Regency, Dwitya Suprijono said these were
the 1st cases chikungunya that have happened in Pangenrejo Village.
"Therefore, this case was determined as an extraordinary incident in
Pangenrejo Village," he said, on Friday [5 Dec 2008].

During 2008 up until now, the chikungunya outbreak always happened in urban
areas in the Nelson Sub district and Purworejo. In general, affected
sufferers were sick for a week.

To the sufferers, Dwitya said, his organization has distributed medicine.
"Further, as efforts to prevent the proliferation of mosquitoes, we will
also do fogging and distribute abate," he said. [Abate is a mosquito
larvicide. - Mod.TY] Dwitya said the most important action to prevent the
spread of the illness is by means of carrying out the eradication of
mosquitoes and to always maintain cleanliness of the environment.

As with dengue fever [virus], chikungunya [virus] is also spread by _Aedes
aegypti_ mosquitoes. In the inspection that was carried out by the team
from the Health Service yesterday [4 Dec 2008], in 53 per cent of the 26
houses that were visited, mosquitoes were found [breeding].

--
communicated by:
